  "prompt": "What should I put on sweet potato fries?",
  "response": "Sweet potato fries can be enhanced in a variety of delicious ways. Here are some popular options for toppings and seasonings:\n\n1. **Classic Seasoning**:\n   - **Salt and Pepper**: A light sprinkle of sea salt and freshly ground black pepper enhances their natural sweetness.\n   - **Garlic Powder**: A touch of garlic can add a savory depth of flavor.\n\n2. **Herbs and Spices**:\n   - **Paprika or Smoked Paprika**: Adds a subtle smokiness or mild heat.\n   - **Cinnamon and Sugar**: For a sweet version, mix cinnamon with a bit of sugar and sprinkle over the fries.\n\n3. **Cheesy Toppings**:\n   - **Parmesan Cheese**: Grated or shredded Parmesan adds a savory, nutty flavor.\n   - **Cheddar Cheese**: Melt some cheddar over the top for a gooey, indulgent delight.\n\n4. **Fresh Herbs**:\n   - **Rosemary or Thyme**: Chop fresh rosemary or thyme and sprinkle over the fries after cooking.\n   - **Cilantro or Parsley**: Adds freshness and a burst of flavor.\n\n5. **Sauces and Dips**:\n   - **Ketchup or Spicy Ketchup**: A classic choice, with a spicy twist if desired.\n   - **Aioli or Garlic Mayo**: Creamy dips like aioli complement the fries well.\n   - **Honey Mustard**: Sweet and tangy, this pairs nicely with sweet potato fries.\n   - **Sriracha or Hot Sauce**: For those who like it spicy.\n\n6. **Extras**:\n   - **Bacon Bits**: Crumbled bacon can add a crunchy, salty element.\n   - **Drizzle of Honey or Maple Syrup**: For an extra sweet treat.\n\nFeel free to experiment with combinations of these toppings to find your perfect flavor profile!",
